comments: Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in Jones's (NOP) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Williamson (NOP) is drawn into the air on the pump fake toward DeRozan (CHI) and initiates contact that affects DeRozan's SQBR as he is passing the ball.
Vucevic (CHI) is firming up over his left leg and absorbs the contact from Jones (NOP) to his upper body prior to any leg to leg contact.
Valanciunas (NOP) is moving alongside DeRozan's (CHI) path and he absorbs the marginal contact as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Williamson (NOP) is already in LaVine's (CHI) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Caruso (CHI) brings his hand towards Ingram's (NOP) front and marginal contact occurs off ball.
Ingram (NOP) moves his pivot foot heel-to-toe to create distance.
Ingram (NOP) fully extends his off-arm into Caruso's (CHI) upper body and initiates contact that affects Caruso's ability to defend the drive.
Caruso (CHI) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt.

Jones (NOP) moves laterally into DeRozan's (CHI) body and initiates contact as he defends the driving shot attempt.  Additionally, this contact occurs prior to and causes any ensuing contact from DeRozan.

As DeRozan (CHI) raises his arms to shoot, some contact occurs with Jones' (NOP) head.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
LaVine (CHI) and Ingram (NOP) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Ingram (NOP) is already in Dragic's (CHI) path and he absorbs the contact that occurs during the pick.
LaVine (CHI) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Jones (NOP) places his left hand on DeRozan's (CHI) hip, and marginal contact occurs as Jones' right hand makes clean contact with the ball on the perimeter.
Jones (NOP) is moving alongside DeRozan's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Williamson (NOP) is already in LaVine's (CHI) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
LaVine (CHI) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Williamson (NOP) jumps vertically and the marginal contact is caused as DeRozan (CHI) slightly extends his forearm towards Williamson during his driving shot attempt.
DeRozan (CHI) and Jones (NOP) briefly engage and disengage as marginal lower body contact occurs during rebounding.
LaVine (CHI) moves laterally into Williamson's (NOP) path and initiates body contact that affects Williamson's SQBR.
Vucevic (CHI) is already in McCollum's (NOP) path and he absorbs the contact as he firms up during the screen.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: DeRozan (CHI) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Pelicans.
Williamson (NOP) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Green's (CHI) left hand makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Jones (NOP) on the perimeter.
Jones Jr. (CHI) commits a take foul on Jones (NOP).
Dragic (CHI) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot and he slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
DeRozan (CHI) commits take foul on Jones (NOP). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Jones (NOP) cleanly deflects the ball away from Caruso (CHI) and Vucevic (CHI) during rebounding.
